    "content": "nullReport and Reduce Your Carbon Footprint with Net Zero Cloud\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Report and Reduce Your Carbon Footprint with Net Zero Cloud\n Get Ready to Use Net Zero Cloud\n Determine the Sources to Inventory\n Emissions Factors That Affect Calculations\n Create Your Consumption Records\n Energy Use Records\n Create a Stationary Asset Energy Use Record\n Create a Vehicle Asset Energy Use Record\n Create a Freight Hauling Energy Use Record\n Create a Rental Car Energy Use Record\n Create an Air Travel Energy Use Record\n Create a Hotel Stay Energy Use Record\n Create a Ground Travel Energy Use Record\n Create a Scope 3 Procurement Summary Record\n Create a Generated Waste Record\n Conditions for Automatic Creation of Carbon Footprints\n Manage Scope 3 Value Chain Data\n Manage Your Carbon Footprint\n Manage Your Water Footprint\n Manage the Annual Emissions Inventory\n Record Locking and Recalculation\n Benchmark Building Energy Intensity Data\n Manage Carbon Footprint Data Gaps\n Set Emissions Targets\n Emissions Forecasting\n Carbon Accounting for Extended Organizational Boundaries\n Carbon Accounting for Partner Community Users\n Engage Suppliers for Emissions Reduction\n Allocate Carbon Credits to Offset Unavoidable Emissions\n Allocate Energy Attribute Certificate Credits to Reduce Scope 2...\n Report Social and Governance Data with Net Zero Cloud\n Generate Disclosures by Using Disclosure and Compliance Hub\n Data Collection\n Improve Decarbonization Strategy with Sustainability Programs\n Data Auditing\n Submit Records for Approval\n Use Net Zero Analytics App\n Use DEI Analytics App\n Report Your Carbon Footprint\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nREPORT AND REDUCE YOUR CARBON FOOTPRINT WITH NET ZERO CLOUD\nCreate Your Consumption Records\n\nUse your utility bills and travel records to record the energy consumption for your assets and travel activities. Create individual records for energy usage for any reporting period such as weekly, monthly, or yearly.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\nAvailable in: Lightning Experience\nAvailable in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions\nIMPORTANT Only the user who created the asset or footprint records or who has either View All or Modify All access to the records can view the records in the lookup fields. To enable a user to view records created by other users, your Salesforce administrator must enable the View All or Modify All access for the user on the required objects. For more information about setting permissions, see Troubleshoot Object and Record Access Issues.\nNOTE By default, only your Salesforce administrator can delete records. However, you can delete records if you have Modify All access or your Salesforce administrator can grant delete access to users for the objects.\nEnergy Use Records\nThe energy use record determines the consumption data type that you enter. Though optional fields in an energy use record aren’t used for calculations, you can enter information in these fields to trigger auto-calculations. Altering the emissions factors of energy use records don’t change or recalculate the record.\nCreate a Stationary Asset Energy Use Record\nCreate a record for each reporting or billing period per stationary asset.\nCreate a Vehicle Asset Energy Use Record\nCreate a record for each reporting period or fueling record for each fleet vehicle. You can aggregate the fuel used and the distance traveled over multiple trips into a single record. For owned assets, emissions are calculated as scope 1. For leased assets, emissions are calculated as scope 3.\nCreate a Freight Hauling Energy Use Record\nCreate a record for movement of freight by air, rail, sea, or road. The freight hauling mode must match the mode chosen on the freight hauling emissions factor record. Net Zero Cloud automatically performs any unit conversions necessary for calculations.\nCreate a Rental Car Energy Use Record\nCreate a rental car record for each rental car. Rental cars are scope 3 category, so rental car energy use records must match the rental car emissions factors.\nCreate an Air Travel Energy Use Record\nCreate a record for all air travel in each reporting period. Associate an air travel record with a vehicle asset to track emissions by region.\nCreate a Hotel Stay Energy Use Record\nCreate a record for each individual hotel stay. Associate a hotel stay record with a stationary asset record.\nCreate a Ground Travel Energy Use Record\nTo track emissions by region, associate ground travel records with a scope 3 asset. Create a record for each ground travel type and each reporting period. Ground travel is a scope 3 category, so ground travel energy use records must match the ground travel emissions factors record. The ground travel record types are personal car, taxi, limousine, and subway, train, or trolley. In calculations, Net Zero Cloud treats taxis and limousines identically and the subway, train, and trolley choices identically. All calculations require ground travel emissions factors.\nCreate a Scope 3 Procurement Summary Record\nCreate a record represents the amount that the organization spends for an individual procurement category. Scope 3 procurement summary quantifies the effect on atmospheric warming, represented in tonnes of carbon dioxide equivalent (tCO₂e) by using a matched emissions factor from an associated Procurement Emissions Factor Item record.\nCreate a Generated Waste Record\nCreate a record for all the waste generated in operations, the waste generated while treating end-of-life products that were sold, and other types of generated waste.\nConditions for Automatic Creation of Carbon Footprints\nWhen an energy use record is created without the carbon footprint information, you can set the Net Zero Cloud configuration options to automatically assign or create a carbon footprint.\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
